So, it looks to me like the important parts are:
Vendor 3223 (decimal), Product 8, and Interface 1 for the serial port.

so, then we try:
# kextload /System/Library/Extensions/FTDIUSBSerialDriver.kext

which looks like it loaded a driver, kernel.log: 
kernel[0]: FTDIUSBSerialDriver:        0  c970008 start - ok

Which makes a horribly named PSR-800gobblidlygook name.  It has to be as long as or longer than "usbserial".. shiiiiity driver code.

